'''德里克·迈克尔·肖万'''（{{lang-en|Derek Michael Chauvin}}，{{IPAc-en|'|ʃ|oʊ|v|ən}} {{Respell|SHOH|vən}}，{{bd|1976年|3月19日|catIdx=R}}）是[[美国|美国]]前警官，因涉嫌串謀在[[明尼苏达州|明尼苏达州]][[明尼阿波利斯|明尼阿波利斯]][[乔治·弗洛伊德之死|杀害乔治·弗洛伊德]]被判入獄22年6個月<ref>{{Cite news|title=Derek Chauvin is found guilty of murdering George Floyd.|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/04/20/us/chauvin-guilty-murder-george-floyd.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2021-04-20|accessdate=2021-04-20|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Tim|last=Arango|first2=Shaila|last2=Dewan|first3=John|last3=Eligon|first4=Nicholas|last4=Bogel-Burroughs|archive-date=2021-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422175203/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/04/20/us/chauvin-guilty-murder-george-floyd.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

在2020年5月25日与其他三名警察进行的逮捕行动中，肖万曾跪在弗洛伊德的脖子上8分46秒，当时弗洛伊德戴着手铐，脸朝下躺在街上，喊着“{{link-en|我无法呼吸|I can't breathe}}”。他于5月26日被{{link-en|明尼阿波利斯警察局|Minneapolis Police Department
}}解雇，5月29日被捕。这起谋杀案在[[明尼阿波利斯-聖保羅都會區|明尼阿波利斯-聖保羅都會區]]和美国其他地区掀起了[[乔治·弗洛伊德之死引发的示威活动|一系列抗议活动]]，后来[[乔治·弗洛伊德之死在美国以外引发的示威列表|蔓延到世界各地]]。肖万被指控犯有二级非故意谋杀罪、三级谋杀罪和二级过失杀人罪。

他的谋杀案审判于2021年3月8日在明尼苏达州第四司法区法院开始，并于4月20日结束，陪审团裁定他三项罪名成立。在[[亨内平县|亨内平县]]法官彼得·A·卡希尔（{{lang|en|Peter A. Cahill}}）接受了检方的动议后，他的[[保释|保释]]被撤销。他被关押在{{link-en|橡树园高地监狱|Oak Park Heights prison|橡树园高地最高安全监狱}}，直到他在6月25日被判刑<ref>{{cite web|author=WCCO-TV Staff|date=2021-04-27|title=Derek Chauvin's Sentencing Rescheduled For June 25|url=https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2021/04/27/derek-chauvins-sentencing-rescheduled-for-june-25/|work=CBS Minnesota|access-date=2021-05-08|archive-date=2021-05-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513021204/https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2021/04/27/derek-chauvins-sentencing-rescheduled-for-june-25/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2021年5月12日，法院裁定，由于乔文使用了严重的武力，检方可以寻求更长的刑期<ref>{{cite news|last=Wamsley|first=Laurel|date=2021-05-12|title=Judge Finds Aggravating Factors In Chauvin Case, Paving Way For Longer Sentence|url=https://www.npr.org/2021/05/12/996158514/judge-finds-aggravating-factors-in-chauvin-case-opening-path-for-longer-sentence|work=NPR|access-date=2021-05-12|archive-date=2021-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627213803/https://www.npr.org/2021/05/12/996158514/judge-finds-aggravating-factors-in-chauvin-case-opening-path-for-longer-sentence|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2021年6月25日，他被判处22.5年监禁，有可能在服刑三分之二或因二级谋杀罪服刑15年后被监管释放<ref>{{Cite web|last=CNN|first=Eric Levenson and Ray Sanchez|date=2021-06-25|title=Derek Chauvin sentenced to 22.5 years in death of George Floyd|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/06/25/us/derek-chauvin-sentencing-george-floyd/index.html|dead-url=no|access-date=2021-06-25|website=CNN|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628015614/https://www.cnn.com/2021/06/25/us/derek-chauvin-sentencing-george-floyd/index.html}}</ref>。

蕭文在2001年至2020年期间是明尼阿波利斯警察局的成员，并于2006年毕业于{{link-en|大都会州立大学|Metropolitan State University}}，获得[[执法|执法]]学士学位。

== 早年生活 ==
德里克·肖万出生于1976年3月19日<ref name="27-CDR-20-12646">{{cite web|url=https://www.hennepinattorney.org/-/media/Attorney/Derek-Chauvin-Criminal-Complaint.pdf|title=Complaint – ''State of Minnesota v. Derek Michael Chauvin''|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530173331/https://www.hennepinattorney.org/-/media/Attorney/Derek-Chauvin-Criminal-Complaint.pdf|archive-date=2020-05-30|website=Minnesota District Court, Fourth Judicial District|quote=File No. 27-CR-20-12646|date=2020-05-29|accessdate=2021-04-23|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=barker_06092020>{{cite news|last1=Barker|first1=Kim|last2=Furber|first2=Matt|date=2020-06-09|title=Bail Is at Least $1 Million for Ex-Officer Accused of Killing George Floyd: Derek Chauvin is charged with second-degree murder and second-degree manslaughter in Mr. Floyd's death.|newspaper=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/08/us/derek-chauvin-court.html|access-date=2021-04-23|quote=Mr. Chauvin, who is 44, did not always want to be a police officer.|archive-date=2021-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422010040/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/08/us/derek-chauvin-court.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他的母親是家庭主婦，父親是註冊會計師。父母在他七歲那年離婚，擁有對他的共同監護權<ref name="BarkerKovaleski">{{cite news|last1=Barker|first1=Kim|last2=Kovaleski|first2=Serge F.|title=Officer Who Pressed His Knee on George Floyd's Neck Drew Scrutiny Long Before|date=2020-07-18|newspaper=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/18/us/derek-chauvin-george-floyd.html|access-date=2021-04-23|archive-date=2021-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422010122/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/07/18/us/derek-chauvin-george-floyd.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

肖万曾就讀於明尼蘇達州{{en-link|科蒂奇格罗夫|Cottage Grove}}的派克高中，沒有完成學業，後來獲得了[[普通教育發展證書|普通教育發展證書]]（GED證書）<ref name="Mark"/>。他在達科他郡立技術學院獲得了定量食品準備證書，隨後在[[麥當勞|麥當勞]]及南方地鐵自助餐廳擔任預備廚師<ref name=barker_06092020/><ref name=montemayor_08082020>{{cite news|first1=Stephen|last1=Montemayor|first2=Jennifer|last2=Bjorhus|first3=Matt|last3=McKinney|title=Even to friends, former officer Derek Chauvin was an enigma|date=2020-08-08|newspaper=Star Tribune|url=https://www.startribune.com/those-who-know-derek-chauvin-say-they-would-not-have-predicted-his-killing-of-george-floyd/572054552/|access-date=2021-04-23|archive-date=2021-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422054936/https://www.startribune.com/those-who-know-derek-chauvin-say-they-would-not-have-predicted-his-killing-of-george-floyd/572054552/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。他於1996年至2004年在美國陸軍預備役任職<ref name=levitz_06212020>{{cite news|first1=Jennifer|last1=Levitz|first2=Erin|last2=Ailworth|first3=Tawnell D.|last3=Hobbs|title=George Floyd and Derek Chauvin: The Lives of the Victim and His Killer|date=2020-06-21|newspaper=The Wall Street Journal|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/george-floyd-and-derek-chauvin-the-lives-of-the-victim-and-his-killer-11592761495|access-date=2021-04-23|quote=He also served in the Army Reserve as a military police officer from 1996 to 2004.|archive-date=2021-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210422034729/https://www.wsj.com/articles/george-floyd-and-derek-chauvin-the-lives-of-the-victim-and-his-killer-11592761495|dead-url=no}}</ref>，1996年至2000年期間曾在軍事警察中任職兩次<ref name="Mark"/><ref name="bbc2020-06-08">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52969205|title=George Floyd: What we know about the officers charged over his death|work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|date=2020-06-08|access-date=2021-04-23|quote=Prior to his career in the police, Mr Chauvin served two stints in the US Army. He was a member of the military police from September 1996 to February 1997, and again from September 1999 to May 2000. His other previous jobs include security guard and McDonald's employee.|archive-date=2020-06-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200616115837/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-52969205|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="mprn">{{cite web|url=https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/06/03/cop-in-floyd-death-got-medals-for-valor-and-drew-complaints|title=Cop in Floyd death got medals for valor and drew complaints|website=MPR News|date=2020-06-03|accessdate=2021-04-23|archive-date=2021-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210412185233/https://www.mprnews.org/story/2020/06/03/cop-in-floyd-death-got-medals-for-valor-and-drew-complaints|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在此期間，他還於1995年至1999年就讀於因弗山社區學院，後來轉入大都會州立大學，並於2006年以法律學士學位畢業<ref name="Mark">{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com.au/derek-chauvin-minneapolis-police-background-life-2020-6|title=18 complaints in 19 years, and a murder charge: What we know about ex-Minneapolis police officer Derek Chauvin|first=Michelle|last=Mark|date=2020-06-10|website=Business Insider Australia|accessdate=2021-04-23|archive-date=2021-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421163446/https://www.businessinsider.com.au/derek-chauvin-minneapolis-police-background-life-2020-6|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=montemayor_08082020/><ref name=levitz_06212020/>。

==谋杀和过失杀人案==
=== 乔治·弗洛伊德谋杀案 ===
{{main|乔治·弗洛伊德之死}}
2020年5月25日，肖萬是参与逮捕[[乔治·弗洛伊德|乔治·弗洛伊德]]的四名警察之一，弗洛伊德涉嫌在市場上使用偽造的20美元鈔票，肖萬是其他警察的現場訓練警官<ref>{{cite news|last1=Barker|first1=Kim|title=The Black Officer Who Detained George Floyd Had Pledged to Fix the Police|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/27/us/minneapolis-police-officer-kueng.html|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|access-date=2020-09-03|date=2020-06-27|archive-date=2021-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210427083430/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/06/27/us/minneapolis-police-officer-kueng.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。附近一家商店的监控录像顯示弗洛伊德并未拒絕逮捕<ref>{{cite news|last=Quinlivan|first=Mark|date=2020-05-29|title=George Floyd death: Newly emerged surveillance footage shows no evidence of resistance|work=[[Newshub|Newshub]]|access-date=2020-05-30|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/05/george-floyd-death-newly-emerged-surveillance-footage-shows-no-evidence-of-resistance.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200530095542/https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/world/2020/05/george-floyd-death-newly-emerged-surveillance-footage-shows-no-evidence-of-resistance.html|archive-date=2020-05-30|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Andone|first=Dakin|date=2020-05-28|title=Surveillance video does not support police claims that George Floyd resisted arrest|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|access-date=2020-05-28|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/28/us/video-george-floyd-contradict-resist-trnd/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200528232542/https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/28/us/video-george-floyd-contradict-resist-trnd/index.html|archive-date=2020-05-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。刑事訴狀称，根据[[执法记录仪|执法记录仪]]的录像，弗洛伊德站在警车外时反复说他无法呼吸，因拒絕上警車而被警察過肩摔面朝下摔倒在地<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/02/us/kellie-chauvin-divorce-derek-chauvin-trnd/index.html|title=Derek Chauvin's wife requests to change her last name in divorce filing|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|first=Scottie|last=Andrew|date=2020-06-02|access-date=2021-06-28|archive-date=2020-06-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200612021413/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/02/us/kellie-chauvin-divorce-derek-chauvin-trnd/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。當弗洛伊德被戴上手銬並面朝下躺在街道上時，肖萬在弗洛伊德的脖子上以膝蓋壓制了超过九分鐘<ref>{{Cite web|last=Bogel-Burroughs|first=Nicholas|date=2021-04-10|title=Prosecutors Say Derek Chauvin Knelt on George Floyd for 9 minutes 29 seconds|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/30/us/derek-chauvin-george-floyd-kneel-9-minutes-29-seconds.html|access-date=2021-04-12|website=The New York Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410144947/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/30/us/derek-chauvin-george-floyd-kneel-9-minutes-29-seconds.html|archive-date=2021-04-10|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2020/06/17/prosecutors-derek-chauvin-had-knee-on-george-floyd-for-746-not-846/|title=Prosecutors: Derek Chauvin Had Knee On George Floyd For 7:46, Not 8:46|date=2020-06-17|agency=Associated Press|publisher=CBS Minnesota|access-date=2020-07-02|archive-date=2021-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210610174918/https://minnesota.cbslocal.com/2020/06/17/prosecutors-derek-chauvin-had-knee-on-george-floyd-for-746-not-846/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="cnn2020-06-02"/>。肖萬將膝蓋放在弗洛伊德的脖子後，弗洛伊德反复說“我無法呼吸”，“媽媽”和“拜託”（{{lang|en|please}}）{{r|Hauser}}<ref name="cnn2020-06-02">{{cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/01/us/george-floyd-independent-autopsy/index.html|title=Independent autopsy and Minnesota officials say George Floyd's death was homicide|first=Amir|last=Vera|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|date=2020-06-02|accessdate=2021-06-28|archive-date=2020-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200603020016/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/01/us/george-floyd-independent-autopsy/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一部分時間裡，另外兩名警察壓制弗洛伊德的背<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/29/us/george-floyd-new-video-officers-kneel-trnd/index.html|title=New video appears to show three police officers kneeling on George Floyd|last=Murphy|first=Paul P.|date=2020-06-03|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|access-date=2020-06-18|archive-date=2020-06-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200624171354/https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/29/us/george-floyd-new-video-officers-kneel-trnd/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。最後兩分鐘內<ref>{{cite web|date=2020-06-18|title=Prosecutors: Officer had knee on Floyd for 7:46, 1-minute error not expected to impact criminal case|url=https://kstp.com/news/prosecutors-officer-had-knee-on-floyd-for-746-1-minute-error-not-expected-to-impact-criminal-case/5763703/|access-date=2020-07-24|website=KSTP|language=en|archive-date=2020-07-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200729050442/https://kstp.com/news/prosecutors-officer-had-knee-on-floyd-for-746-1-minute-error-not-expected-to-impact-criminal-case/5763703/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，弗洛伊德一動不動，并已没有脉搏<ref>{{cite news|last=Thorbecke|first=Catherine|date=2020-05-29|title=Derek Chauvin had his knee on George Floyd's neck for nearly 9 minutes, complaint says|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/derek-chauvin-knee-george-floyds-neck-minutes-complaint/story?id=70961042|access-date=2020-06-05|work=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605020604/https://abcnews.go.com/US/derek-chauvin-knee-george-floyds-neck-minutes-complaint/story?id=70961042|archive-date=2020-06-05|dead-url=no}}</ref>。旁觀者拍攝現場並廣泛傳播該視頻<ref name=Hauser>{{cite news|last1=Hauser|first1=Christine|title=F.B.I. to Investigate Arrest of Black Man Who Died After Being Pinned by Officer|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/26/us/minneapolis-police-man-died.html|access-date=2020-05-26|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=2020-05-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526143016/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/05/26/us/minneapolis-police-man-died.html|archive-date=2020-05-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

事件發生後的第二天，肖萬和其他涉案警察被解職<ref>{{cite news|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/01/us/derek-chauvin-what-we-know-trnd/index.html|title=Derek Chauvin: What we know about the former officer charged in George Floyd's death|first=Scottie|last=Andrew|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|date=2020-06-01|accessdate=2021-06-28|archive-date=2020-06-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200622164556/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/06/01/us/derek-chauvin-what-we-know-trnd/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。縱使在某些情況下明尼蘇達州允許警察以膝蓋壓制嫌犯脖子的約束，但是法律專家普遍批評肖萬對這項技巧的使用過於嚴苛<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/05/29/george-floyd-experts-say-neck-restraint-allowed-minneapolis-can-kill/5274334002/|title=George Floyd death: Experts say knee-to-neck restraint is dangerous, but Minneapolis allows it|first1=Grace|last1=Hauck|first2=Dennis|last2=Wagner|newspaper=[[USA_Today|USA Today]]|date=2020-05-29|publisher=[[Gannett|Gannett]]|location=Mclean, Virginia|accessdate=2021-06-28|archive-date=2020-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200601132801/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2020/05/29/george-floyd-experts-say-neck-restraint-allowed-minneapolis-can-kill/5274334002/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/28/us/george-floyd-knee-to-neck-excessive-force-trnd/index.html|title=The move used to restrain George Floyd is discouraged by most police. Here's why|first=Scottie|last=Andrew|website=[[CNN|CNN]]|date=2020-05-29|access-date=2021-06-28|archive-date=2020-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200529020211/https://www.cnn.com/2020/05/28/us/george-floyd-knee-to-neck-excessive-force-trnd/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.politifact.com/article/2020/may/29/death-george-floyd-what-you-need-know/|title=The death of George Floyd: What you need to know|date=2020-05-29|first=Bill|last=McCarthy|website=[[PolitiFact|PolitiFact]]|access-date=2021-06-28|archive-date=2021-02-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210220074355/https://www.politifact.com/article/2020/may/29/death-george-floyd-what-you-need-know/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。6月23日明尼阿波利斯警察局長{{link-en|梅德里亚·阿拉东多|Medaria Arradondo}}表示，肖万接受过{{link-en|体位性窒息|Positional asphyxia}}风险方面的培训，並將弗洛伊德的死定義為[[謀殺|謀殺]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Forliti|first1=Amy|date=2020-06-23|title=Minneapolis police chief says Floyd's death was 'murder'|url=https://www.twincities.com/2020/06/23/minneapolis-police-chief-says-floyds-death-was-murder/|newspaper=[[Twin_Cities_Pioneer_Press|Twin Cities Pioneer Press]]|publisher=Media NewsGroup Inc.|location=[[Twin_Cities,_Minnesota|Twin Cities, Minnesota]]|access-date=2020-06-24|archive-date=2021-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210421191355/https://www.twincities.com/2020/06/23/minneapolis-police-chief-says-floyds-death-was-murder/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

